### Test Authentication Endpoints

# Note: Replace localhost:8000 with your server address if different

### 1. Register a new user with email/password
POST http://localhost:8000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123",
  "full_name": "Test User"
}

###

### 2. Login with email/password
POST http://localhost:8000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123"
}

###

### 3. Google Authentication
# First, get a Firebase ID token from your client app
# Then send it to this endpoint
POST http://localhost:8000/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firebase_token": "your-firebase-id-token-here",
  "full_name": "Google User"
}

###

### 4. Get current user info (protected route)
# Replace <your_jwt_token> with the access_token from login/register response
GET http://localhost:8000/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### 5. Test endpoint (no auth required)
GET http://localhost:8000/auth/test

###

### Example: Register, Login, and Access Protected Route

